{"_id":"recur-readdir","_rev":"1-f5d2ff6712d0d4b6f26112a38fd3e8e5","name":"recur-readdir","description":"recursively read all files and directories within a directory","dist-tags":{"latest":"0.0.1"},"versions":{"0.0.1":{"name":"recur-readdir","description":"recursively read all files and directories within a directory","version":"0.0.1","author":{"name":"Dan Neumann","email":"danrodneu@gmail.com","url":"https://github.com/danneu"},"main":"dist/index.js","scripts":{"build":"tsc","build-watch":"tsc -w","test":"cd test && mocha -r ts-node/register ./**/*.ts","patch":"npm version patch && npm publish","minor":"npm version minor && npm publish","major":"npm version major && npm publish","postpublish":"git push origin master --follow-tags","deploy":"git pull --rebase origin master && git push origin master"},"devDependencies":{"@types/chai":"^4.0.4","@types/fs-extra":"^4.0.3","@types/mocha":"^2.2.44","@types/node":"^8.0.50","@types/temp":"^0.8.31","chai":"^4.1.2","fs-extra":"^4.0.2","mocha":"^4.0.1","temp":"^0.8.3","ts-node":"^3.3.0","typescript":"^2.6.1"},"engines":{"node":">=7.x"},"license":"MIT","gitHead":"77954849b73785fddb6e1c1ea6d787ff3b75fe9e","_id":"recur-readdir@0.0.1","_npmVersion":"5.5.1","_nodeVersion":"9.1.0","_npmUser":{"name":"danneu","email":"danrodneu@gmail.com"},"dist":{"integrity":"sha512-Tt9HkLGNRqhpvm5jlXhMEa5TUhnCmnywz/gDkGoFCpKJB9QEY+y0sCdi3G0erK3OWIOzD/SxCnFT2gej2JV6uA==","shasum":"7040195db33830e630763d974b1d0a38cc87e556","tarball":"https://registry.npmjs.org/recur-readdir/-/recur-readdir-0.0.1.tgz","signatures":[{"keyid":"SHA256:jl3bwswu80PjjokCgh0o2w5c2U4LhQAE57gj9cz1kzA","sig":"MEUCIQDzw9idgYks/cJjoJso3CgERAS3AQNbdCMpJiRn71AKRgIgeG01nwPNksVAcsMPQWik3nXJCENKyLh6UIB/W8cJVx8="}]},"maintainers":[{"name":"danneu","email":"danrodneu@gmail.com"}],"_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"s3://npm-registry-packages","tmp":"tmp/recur-readdir-0.0.1.tgz_1510248318437_0.044383972650393844"}}},"readme":"# recur-readdir\n\n    npm install recur-readdir\n\nRecursively enumerate all files and directories within a directory.\n\nReturns a `Map` of absolute file paths to Node's `fs.Stats` object.\n\n```javascript\nconst {crawl, crawlSync} = require('recur-readdir')\nconst {join} = require('path')\n\ncrawl(join(__dirname, 'testDir'))\n    .then(console.log, console.error)\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n- Async: `crawl` (returns a Promise)\n- Sync: `crawlSync`\n\nPass in options as the second argument. Here are the defaults:\n\n```javascript\ncrawl(path, {\n    depth: Infinity,\n    filter: (path, stats) => true\n})\n```\n\nDepth controls how deep to crawl. A depth of `0` returns\nan empty map.\n\n```javascript\n// Only get the files and directories immediately inside the target dir.\ncrawl(path, { depth: 1 })\n```\n\nOnly files/dirs that satisfy the filter will be included in the results.\nThe filter does not stop recursion.\n\nFor example, this crawl will ignore the `.secret` directory\nand return only files:\n\n```javascript\n// .\n// ├── a.txt\n// ├── b.txt\n// ├── nest1\n// │   └── nest2\n// │       └── nested.txt\n// └── .secret\n//    └── password.txt\nconst filter = (path, stats) => {\n    return !path.includes('/.secret/') && stats.isFile()\n}\n\ncrawl(path, { filter }).then(map => Array.from(map.keys()))\n// ['/Users/user/example/a.txt', '/Users/user/example/b.txt', '/Users/user/example/nest1/nest2/nested.txt']\n```\n\n## Why\n\nOther published modules weren't general enough for me.\n\nI didn't just want file nodes, and I wanted a generalized filter\npredicate.","maintainers":[{"name":"danneu","email":"danrodneu@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2022-05-15T13:34:35.715Z","created":"2017-11-09T17:25:18.496Z","0.0.1":"2017-11-09T17:25:18.496Z"},"author":{"name":"Dan Neumann","email":"danrodneu@gmail.com","url":"https://github.com/danneu"},"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"README.md"}